Title: Massive hematuria successfully treated by bladder irrigations with formalin solution.
Abstract: A report is presented on the use of formalin irrigation of the bladder in the management of massive hematuria in patients with inoperable tumors or as a result of radiation therapy. In 7 of 8 patients in whom this method was adopted, bleeding from the bladder stopped completely.
