Title: Myxoma of the mandible treated by peripheral ostectomy and immediate reconstruction: report of case.
Abstract: A case of fibromyxoma of the mandible treated by peripheral ostectomy and immediate bone graft is presented. This procedure maintains mandibular continuity and can be accomplished via the intraoral approach. There is minimal chance for recurrence and excellent functional and esthetic results can be predicted.
