Title: Chronic retrocalcaneal bursitis treated by resection of the calcaneus.
Abstract: Resection of the posterosuperior aspect of the calcaneus was performed on 43 heels, in 35 patients with chronic retrocalcaneal bursitis. Forty heels in 32 patients were reviewed either by a clinical and radiographical examination (35 heels), or by a questionnaire (5 heels) after an average of 6 years (range 1-12 years). Fifty percent of the heels were cured and additionally 20% improved, but when surgery was performed within 1 year, 92% of the heels were either cured or improved. No correlation was found between the result of surgery and the estimated size of the resection made at surgery.
