Title: Complete remission of bone metastasis of bladder cancer treated by cisplatin-etoposide therapy.
Abstract: A case of bone metastasis from TCC of the bladder that attained complete remission by cisplatin-etoposide therapy was reported. The patient was a 68-year-old male, already treated with total cystectomy. At 29 months after operation, bone metastasis in left acetabulum was found. 3 courses of cisplatin-etoposide therapy were started. At 12 weeks after initiating the therapeutic regimen, the tumor mass of left acetabulum had disappeared completely on the computed tomogram.
