Title: A case of unresectable liver metastasis from leiomyosarcoma of the stomach successfully treated by intra hepato-arterial chemotherapy with Infuse-A-Port.
Abstract: This report describes a 55-year-old man who had a curative operation for leiomyosarcoma of the stomach 6 years ago. Unresectable liver metastases was discovered during the second laparotomy and successfully treated by intra hepato-arterial chemotherapy, which included MMC, ADM and Therarubicin with Infuse-A-Port. He remains well presently with a decrease in the size of the liver metastases and no metastasis to any other organs upon investigation by an abdominal CT 2 years and 2 months after the second laparotomy.
