Title: Chromoblastomycosis treated by Mohs micrographic surgery.
Abstract: Mohs micrographic surgery has been used to treat a variety of skin cancers with excellent results. We present a case where the application of this technique was used effectively to treat a lesion of localized cutaneous chromoblastomycosis. One year following the surgery no recurrence has occurred.
