Title: Infantile achalasia treated by pneumatic dilatation.
Abstract: A 4 month old girl with oesophageal achalasia was successfully treated with a single pneumatic dilatation. A subsequent barium swallow showed almost normal oesophageal caliber. During the following eighteen months, vomiting and feeding problems did not recur.
