Title: Regression of an adenocarcinoma of the breast treated by progesteroid agents. Anatomical-clinical study.
Abstract: A 61-year old woman with breast adenocarcinoma was treated with hormonotherapy for 1 year. After this treatment the tumor had regressed and a mastectomy was performed. The macroscopic and histological examinations of the tumor showed similarities between the changes observed in this case and the ones which have been described by Emerson and his colleagues following estrogenotherapy and androgenotherapy in the case of clinically hormone-dependent breast cancers.
