Title: A report of 21 cases of malignant lymphoma treated by radiotherapy.
Abstract: In 1971, 21 new patients with malignant lymphoma were treated at the Therapeutic Radiology Department, Singapore General Hospital. 17 patients completed their courses of radiotherapy. Of the 17 patients given radical treatment, 5 were of Hodgkin's disease and 12 of Non-Hodgkin's disease. The 5-year survival for the group with Hodgkin's disease is 80% (4/5). The 5-year survival for the group with Non-Hodgkin's disease in 41.6% (5/12).
