Title: Three cases of post traumatic vascular headache treated by surgery.
Abstract: Three cases are reported of vascular headache following trauma and which failed to respond adequately to standard therapy for migraine. In each case the effect of ligation of the arteries involved has been dramatic, with complete and lasting relief in two cases.
